to custom sub lisha screen.</p>'),('MT0.10',112,'ENG','sort by order by  : [color=CadetBlue]define_column_lov_order[/color]','<p class=\"title\">Description</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Define order result by column priority in list of values.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">For severals order by, call severals time this function.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">First call define the highest priority and then priority decrease</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Function</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #008080;\">define_column_lov_order</span>(<span style=\"color: #888888;\">column_name</span>,<span style=\"color: #888888;\">order_mode</span>)</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Access&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">write</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Possible values</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">&lt;ipage:96/&gt;,&nbsp;<span>&lt;ipage:97/&gt;</span></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Example</p>\n<p class=\"subtitle\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Write</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>$my_object</strong>-&gt;<span style=\"color: #008080;\">define_column_lov_order</span>(\'C<span style=\"color: #808080;\">olumnName</span>\',<span>&lt;ipage:96/&gt;</span>);</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Default value</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">No default value</p>'),('MT0.10',113,'ENG','rules','<p class=\"title\">Best practice to create main query</p>\n<hr />\n<p class=\"normal\">If you have no <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">WHERE</span> condition in your main query then finish your query with folowing string</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><strong>WHERE 1 = 1</strong></p>\n<hr />\n<p class=\"normal\">Defined specific each field you have to display</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Use <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">SELECT</span> `field1` <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">AS</span> `myfield1`, `field4` <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">AS</span> `myfield2` <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">FROM</span> ...</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">instead of</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">SELECT</span> * <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">FROM</span> ...</p>\n<hr />\n<p class=\"normal\">Add an alias on each table ( except table to update ) and field defined</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">`<strong>BUG</strong>`.`Qui` <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong>AS</strong></span>&nbsp;`<strong>who`</strong>,</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">`<strong>TEX</strong>`.`text` <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong>AS</strong></span>&nbsp;`<strong>status`</strong>,</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">`<strong>BUG</strong>`.`reference` <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong>AS</strong></span>&nbsp;`<strong>reference`</strong>,</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">`<strong>BUG</strong>`.`Last_mod` <span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><strong>AS</strong></span>&nbsp;`<strong>last_mod`</strong></p>\n<hr />\n<p><img class=\"image\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/SRX_main_query_example.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" /></p>'),('MT0.10',122,'ENG','add fast field : [color=CadetBlue]define_fast_field[/color]','<p class=\"title\">Description</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Optional set of couple array (table,column).</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Define set of couple (table_alias_name,column) to provide fast response time in your query.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">You can also use a hidding column name.</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Function</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #008080;\">define_fast_field</span>(</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Array</span>(\'table_name\',column_name1)</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Array</span>(<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">null</span>,column_name2),</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 120px;\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Array</span>(\'table_alias\',column_name3)</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 120px;\">)</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Structure</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Array</span>(\'<span style=\"color: #808080;\">table_name</span>\',\'<span style=\"color: #808080;\">column_name</span>\')</p>\n<table class=\"main_table\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"title\">\n<td class=\"head_table\">Parameters</td>\n<td class=\"head_table\">Type</td>\n<td class=\"head_table\">Default</td>\n<td class=\"head_table\">Description</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"row_table\"><em>table_name</em></td>\n<td class=\"row_table\">string</td>\n<td class=\"row_table\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">null</span></td>\n<td class=\"row_table\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">null</span> means using general table name from &lt;ipage:88 update table name/&gt;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"row_table\"><em>column_name</em></td>\n<td class=\"row_table\">string</td>\n<td class=\"row_table\"><span>mandatory</span></td>\n<td class=\"row_table\">Column name from your &lt;ipage:25 main query/&gt;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p class=\"title\">Access&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">write</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Possible values</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">An existing column name defined in main table</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>and</strong></span></p>\n<p class=\"normal\">column that keep his original name in query.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/SRX_define_fast_field.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/SRX_define_fast_field.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"662\" height=\"683\" /></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Example</p>\n<p class=\"subtitle\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Write</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>$my_object</strong>-&gt;<span style=\"color: #008080;\">define_fast_field</span>(<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Array</span>(\'<span style=\"color: #808080;\">id</span>\',\'<span style=\"color: #808080;\">version</span>\'));</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Default value</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">Array</span>()</p>'),('MT0.10',115,'ENG','title area','<p class=\"title\">Column head title area</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">This area below had 3 differents features.</p>\n<ul class=\"normal\">\n<li>Display column title</li>\n<li>Drag and drop zone to move column position</li>\n<li>Change or define a column order by ( Hold control key pressed to add new sub order by )</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_head_title_area.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_head_title_area.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"208\" height=\"122\" /></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Setup</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">To define title of column, you have to input title value in &lt;ipage44: column definition&gt; on fourth parameters as below.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_title%20feature.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_title%20feature.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"835\" height=\"83\" /></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Tips</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">It\'s possible to have an empty title but features to move or order by column are still actives.</p>'),('MT0.10',116,'ENG','order by area','<p class=\"title\">Column head order by area</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">This area below display order by option if any setup or forced by user.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_head_order_area.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_head_order_area.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"209\" height=\"122\" /></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Ascending or Descending</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Descending mode means from the <span>smallest</span>&nbsp;to the <span>largest</span>. You can see this following icon.</p>\n<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"__blue_ico_sort-ascend\" style=\"background-image: url(\'images/icons/img_16.png\'); height: 20px; width: 18px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p class=\"normal\">Ascending mode means from the largest to the smallest.&nbsp;<span>You can see this following icon.</span></p>\n<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"__blue_ico_sort-descend\" style=\"background-image: url(\'images/icons/img_16.png\'); height: 20px; width: 18px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p class=\"title\">Deep order</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">If you have more than one sorted column then you will see a number as exponent.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">That number provide you priority of you order. Number one have the higest priority.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Order priority is automatically computed. It\'s the seqential order of function call &lt;ipage:95&nbsp;define_order_column/&gt;.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Here below, description field is on the third call position. So priority order is set to three.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_head_order_priority.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_head_order_priority.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"543\" height=\"132\" /></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Function</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">To setup order by, use &lt;ipage:95 order column/&gt; function.</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Tips</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">To remove order by option, use column contextual menu</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span>By program setup, use constante &lt;ipage:117/&gt;</span></p>'),('MT0.10',117,'ENG','__NONE__','<p class=\"title\">Constante name</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #808080;\">__NONE__</span></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Value</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">&gt;&lt;</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Usefull</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">in function &lt;ipage:95 sort by column/&gt;</p>'),('MT0.10',118,'ENG','contextual menu','<p class=\"title\">Column head contextual menu</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">This area display information and provide interactive action with user.</p>\n<p class=\"subtitle\">Standard form</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">It\'s a free marble as below.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu_free_marble.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu_free_marble.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"143\" height=\"96\" /></p>\n<p class=\"subtitle\">Hover</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">That means there is standard contextual menu available.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">If you hover this area, you will see the following icon. That is actif if you left click on this area.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"204\" height=\"101\" /></p>\n<p class=\"normal\">If you have custom matchcode list on column, then a red marble will appears.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu_red_marble.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu_red_marble.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"143\" height=\"104\" /></p>\n<p class=\"normal\">if some filter are turn on you have a different form</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu_filter_on.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu_filter_on.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"129\" height=\"110\" /></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Setup</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">To define title of column, you have to input title value in &lt;ipage44: column definition&gt; on fourth parameters as below.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_title%20feature.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_title%20feature.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"835\" height=\"83\" /></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Tips</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">It\'s possible to have an empty title but features to move or order by column are still actives.</p>'),('MT0.10',119,'ENG','details menu','<p class=\"title\">Column head contextual menu</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">If you right click on contextual button, a new contextual menu windows appears.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><img class=\"image\" onclick=\"window.open(\'doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu_details.png\')\" src=\"doc_tech/picture/column_head_context_menu_details.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"173\" height=\"205\" /></p>\n<p class=\"normal\">If you left click on contextual menu button, custom or standard distinct values available on this column will appear.</p>'),('MT0.10',120,'ENG','date rules','<p class=\"title\">Wizard on column type date</p>\n<hr />\n<p class=\"normal\">if no date format defined on column then use default system date format depend on your localization.</p>'),('MT0.10',121,'ENG','quick search mode : [color=CadetBlue]__active_quick_search[/color]','<p class=\"title\">Description</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Active or not quick search on column head input area.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Quick search send request to server then you start to type something in column head input area.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">If you have a huge table, this function can be slow and unefficient. So, you can disable it.</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Function</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #008080;\">__active_quick_search</span></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Access&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"normal\">Read Write</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Possible values</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">true</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #808080;\">&nbsp;</span>: Quick search is on.</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">false</span>&nbsp;: Quick search if off.</p>\n<p class=\"title\">Example</p>\n<p class=\"subtitle\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Write</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>$my_object</strong>-&gt;<span style=\"color: #808080;\">define_attribute</span>(\'<span style=\"color: #008080;\">__active_quick_search</span>\', <span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">true</span>);</p>\n<p class=\"subtitle\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Read</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">echo</span><strong> $my_object</strong>-&gt;<span style=\"color: #808080;\">read_attribute</span>(\'<span style=\"color: #008080;\">__active_quick_search</span>\');</p>\n<p class=\"normal\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">will return <span style=\"color: #ff6600;\">true</span></p>\n<p class=\"title\">Default value</p>\n<p class=\"normal\"><span>true</span></p>');
